            <thetext>If a macro is defined within a job&#39;s &quot;let&quot; section like so:

    &quot;source&quot; :
    {
      &quot;let&quot; :
      {
        &quot;FOO&quot; : &quot;bar&quot;
      }
    }

overriding its value on the shell, e.g.

generate.py source -m FOO:somethingelse

does not work. Running the generator with the -w flag shows that the value of $FOO is still &quot;bar&quot;.

If a macro is defined in the config file&#39;s top-level &quot;let&quot; section, however, it can be overridden from the shell as expected.</thetext>
